title: 31 Days of Andi Mack
body:
Day 15:  Favorite Headcanon about your favorite ship or brotp?

my favorite tyrus headcanon is that whenever they go out on dates and someone mistakes them for being “really good friends :)” tj goes out of his way to give a long rant about how “actually, we’re boyfriends :)) see how i hold his hand and kiss his cheek and how we’re in love? :)))” until the person - usually a random, unassuming stranger - gets uncomfortable and leaves and cyrus blushes and tells him to stop antagonizing people for no reason, but is really uwu over how unapologetic tj is about their relationship

summary: 31 Days of Andi Mack - Day 13
title: 31 Days of Andi Mack - Day 13
body:
Whoops! I have fallen off the wagon a bit, and these have not been posted on the proper day due to work and technical difficulties. Playing catch up, so apologies.

What’s one thing you are hoping to happen in Season 3?

One thing I wish would happen more in season 3 is for Andi to have story lines with Cyrus and Buffy, together or separate, like Cyrus and Buffy have with each other. Too often Andi is given story lines with relationship drama, and another large portion of her screen time is delegated to her family arcs. However, it cause a disconnect with me. Yes, I know Andi is friends with Cyrus and Buffy, but if we hardly see her have a solo arc with them not focusing on her questioning romantic relationships, I just will not feel she is as close with them as she once was. Season one did an okay job at balancing these arcs, but season two left Andi on an island separated from her friends for most of the season.
